body_html:
When fetching an output, all the placeholders required in order to compute the output need to be fetched. Looking at your model, it seems likely that in order to compute OUTPUT_NODES (i.e., the tensor named y_), you need to feed the input and the keep_prob placeholder, defined in your Python model in the line:

keep_prob = tf.placeholder(tf.float32)

Long story short, either change your Python model so that keep_prob isn't a placeholder but rather a constant. Or feed a value for it using inferenceInterface.feed().

Hope that helps.
I'm going to close this issue since this question is better asked on StackOverflow as it is not a bug or feature request.

body:
When fetching an output, all the placeholders required in order to compute the output need to be fetched. Looking at your model, it seems likely that in order to compute `OUTPUT_NODES` (i.e., the tensor named `y_`), you need to feed the input and the `keep_prob` placeholder, defined in your Python model in the line:

```python
keep_prob = tf.placeholder(tf.float32)
```

Long story short, either change your Python model so that `keep_prob` isn't a placeholder but rather a constant. Or feed a value for it using `inferenceInterface.feed()`.

Hope that helps.
I'm going to close this issue since this question is better asked on  [StackOverflow](http://stackoverflow.com/questions/tagged/tensorflow) as it is not a  bug or feature request.
